title: For Sale/Trade:  COP-INC .38 / .357
postcontent: SALE OR TRADE - VERY RARE - COP .357 / .38 4 barrel derringer.   The COP 357 is a very rare pistol that is no longer in production. Made famous in the movie "Blade Runner" and seen in such movies as "Bad Boys", "The Matrix Reloaded",and most recently "21 Jump Street" the COP would be a welcomed piece to any collectors collection.  Easy to fire and easy on the eyes this rare pistol has 4 barrels which fire 357 magnums or .38 specials. The COP 357 is a 4 shot Derringer type pistol chambered for the powerful .357 Magnum round. It was designed by Robert Hillberg, based on his earlier work on the Hillberg Insurgency Weapon. It was manufactured by the now defunct COP Inc. of 3040 West Lomita Blvd., Torrance, California (COP stood for Compact Off-Duty Police). The double action weapon is about twice as wide, and substantially heavier than the typical .25 automatic pistol (@ 1.75LBS)  - it is solid stainless steel.  Each of the four chambers has its own dedicated firing pin. It uses an internal hammer, which is activated by depressing the trigger to hit a ratcheting/rotating striker that in turn strikes one firing pin at a time. Older "pepperboxes" also used multiple barrels, but the barrels were the part that rotated. The COP 357 operates similarly to the Sharps rimfire pepperbox of the 1850s, in that it uses the ratcheting/rotating striker, which is completely internal, to fire each chamber in sequence.  This piece has a very light professional inscription (see pic) of the name "Tom Balding".  Comes with case and 4 rounds of .357.  $1000 or Trade.  Steve - Frisco.

title: Want To Buy:  Springfield firearms
postcontent:
Ok so pretty much everyone here is an American . I think you'd all agree that we love our country and we love firearms . With the years of warfare winding down , our veterans are returning home and the economy is improving at a good rate .

My father always liked springfield armory weapons . As they say like father like son . However, with the current state of the company he's rolling over in his grave . Springfield proudly proclaims they are the oldest firearms manufacturer in America . 

This is all well and good . However with our economy in the toilet you can't outsource jobs to places like Brazil and Croatia . They claim to care about America . There are thousands of qualified vets from gunsmiths to machinists looking for work . These guys aren't looking for a handout but a hand up . They are qualified and hard working . Instead springfield keeps their company HQ here to catch huge tax breaks while shipping jobs overseas .

The price point of their weapons should reflect what goes into them . This basically amounts to cutting corners and half assing things . All the while digging into our pockets and not putting anything back in the pockets of our brothers and sisters who want nothing more than to get back to work .

I came across this petition on change.org 
http://www.change.org/petitions/springfield-armory-stop-manufacturing-weapons-in-brazil-and-put-more-americans-to-work-here?recruiter=84921913&utm_campaign=signature_receipt&utm_medium=email&utm_source=share_petition
Please sign it . There are only two signatures so please share it . I believe this man is right I say we boycott springfield until some changes are made . Maybe they could have avoided recalls by hiring workers with higher skill sets . This is shady on springfields part . If they like Brazil so much move the corporate office to São Paulo .thanks for reading and your time please share the link . Let's get this ship back on course before it's too late . I understand a small percentage of their weapons are made here . Small doesn't cut it with me . We are the consumers if we demand things and stand together it will happen . 

I don't have a problem with paying 1,000 dollars for a weapon made here . I know that me purchasing American helped feed a family and kept them working here not in Brazil . Call me a xenophobe but America comes first unless of course you're the folks over at Springfield Armory .

This is one of the reasons why our great cities are crumbling . Cities like Detroit , Pittsburgh etc . I say we stop letting these manufactures buy Brazilian steel and create jobs there not here . We should not contribute to this I'm afraid the blame is squarely on us . Some may not care but this is a big deal . Who buys the most guns folks ?. Us so no matter what you think we do have a say in this .

postcontent:
WTS: Custom Springfield Armory XDS, .45ACP in Massachusetts!!!

This is the smallest, lightest, slimmest 45 auto on the market, and in spite of it all it’s remarkably easy to shoot.  I’ve carried this gun for about a year, shot it very little, round count is around 200 rounds.  It’s a great gun, slim, light and easy to carry, but I built an RMR equipped XDm 3.8 and am carrying that instead, so the XDS just sits in the safe now.

I sent this gun to Powder River Precision to have them install their spring kit, tune the mag release and perform their Carry grip work (actual grip texture, not the stick-on grip tape).  Trigger is a nice crisp #4.5.  It also features the factory fiber optic front sight.

The gun comes with the complete XD Gear kit, including 2 mags, holster, mag carrier, case, etc., etc. 

This is a pre-recall gun and I’ve chosen not to send it to Springfield for the optional modification.  There are a lot of people choosing to keep their guns stock and since there seems to be enough demand out there, I figured I’d offer the gun for sale unmodified.  Of course, buyer is welcome to send it to Springfield for free, and as a bonus, Springfield will also give you a free 7 round extended magazine when they return your gun.

Asking $750 OBO, FTF on FA-10 in the greater Boston/metrowest area.  Buyer must have Class A LTC.  All laws to be followed.

I will entertain trade offers, but the only trades I'm definitely interested in are a Beretta CX4 Storm carbine (9mm, 92FS mags), a Kriss Vector or a USGI M1 Carbine (IBM or Rockola).

Pictures are stock, will upload actual pictures as soon as I'm able.

*****

Standard Terms:
I am not a firearms dealer engaged in the business of buying and selling guns, I am merely a collector who occasionally sells a firearm from his personal collection.

All local, state and Federal laws are to be strictly followed. For those who are unsure of how to conduct a private transaction, I'm happy to answer questions and walk you through the process. However, any requests to violate the law will immediately end negotiations.

I prefer to conduct the majority of negotiations over PM, email or text. I'm not trying to be elusive, I just prefer a written record of our agreement.

I am happy to answer any and all questions to be best of my ability, however, please do your own research - I'm not a salesman.

All negotiations are to be conducted via email, text or phone call before the transaction. Once we reach a deal, negotiations are closed. If you show up to the transaction after we've made a deal and try to weasel another $50 out of me, I'll walk away.

You cannot "try it out" to see if you like the gun. I am not a walking show room. If we happen to be at the same range at the same time, and I have the gun that's for sale with me, I'll probably be willing to let you to try it out, but this is the exception, not the rule.

I cannot stress this one enough: when we reach an agreement (which could be as simple as "I'll take it" and "it's yours,") you've entered into a contract to complete the transaction. Unless the item is not as described (I take pains to make sure I fairly describe anything I sell, and I'll allow you all the time and leeway you need to inspect it), you're expected to show up when and where we agree and complete the transaction.

I reserve the right to sell to whomever I wish.

Please don't write "call me" with nothing else in your email. I'm not going to call you if I have no indication of your level of interest, if you want to make an offer, or what your questions might be.

Please don't ask, "Is it still available? with nothing else in your email. That's just a waste of everyone's time.

I reserve the right to ignore ridiculous offers.

title: For Sale:  Timney AR10 Trigger w/4 lbs pull - brand new never used
postcontent:
I have a brand new Timney Trigger for an AR10 (#670) - I bought this for my 308 build but my lower has a shelf in it that keeps this trigger from sitting flat. Because it won't sit flat I cannot get the trigger and hammer pin holes to line up. The packaging has been opened but the trigger comes complete with everything original included. I dropped it in the lower, it didn't fit, I took it out, as quick as that.

I talked to Timney tech support (awesome BTW) and they said that my lower is proprietary and the shelf is to prevent a normal trigger group from over rotating. Not an issue with the Timney trigger. They said this trigger is made to work with any millspec 308 lower, and mine is not millspec.

I paid $250 for this and I am letting it go for $200 - my loss, your gain

Thanks for looking
